01/08/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul met on Thursday (31 July) with Britain's special representative to Iraq, John Sawers. The envoy expressed full support for the idea of Turkey sending peacekeeping troops to Iraq. Gul said the decision to dispatch troops would need the approval of both the government and parliament.
In other developments, Israel will participate in a joint military exercise with the United States and Turkey. This sixth joint air and sea exercise will be conducted in international waters off the coast of southern Turkey. (Anadolu Agency, TRT 2 - 31/07/03)
